==Parameters==
All fields are optional because they use [[mw:Help:Extension:ParserFunctions|ParserFunctions]], which allow fields to be hidden if no value is set. The infobox is segmented into several basic parts, including the name of the site, an image, a map of the site's location, basic information about the site, and information pertaining to the registers on which the site is listed. Wikilinks and other formatting are acceptable in any of the Infobox fields except map/image and coordinate parameters.

Please spend some time at the [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Historic sites|Historic sites WikiProject]] and its [[Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Historic sites|talk page]] for standards on presenting names, designations, and other data.

{{Infobox historic site
| name = Arles Obelisk
| native_name = Obélisque d'Arles
| native_language = French
| image = Arles obelisque.jpg
| caption = The Arles Obelisk in front of the Arles town hall (right)
| designation1 = WHS
| designation1_date = 1981 <small>(5th [[:en:World Heritage Committee|session]])</small>
| designation1_partof = [[:en:Arles, Roman and Romanesque Monuments|Arles, Roman and Romanesque Monuments]]
| designation1_number = [http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/164 164]
| designation1_criteria = ii, iv
| designation1_type = Cultural
| designation1_free1name = Region
| designation1_free1value = [[:en:List of World Heritage Sites in Europe|Europe and North America]]
| designation2 = Monument historique
| designation2_date = 1840
| designation2_number = PA00081180
| designation2_offname = Obélisque antique
| location = Place de la République<br/>13200 [[:en:Arles, France|Arles, France]]
| height= {{convert|15.26|m}}<br/>With pedestal: {{convert|19.81|m}}
| built = 4th century
| rebuilt = March 26, 1676
| architect = Jacques Peytret
| coordinates = {{coord|43.67636|4.627594|display=inline}}
| locmapin = France
| map_relief = yes
}}

===Basic information===
Basic information consists of information that can apply to any site, regardless of what it has been designated. This includes information like the site's location; when the site was built, formed, or founded; and information about who built it and how it was built. Basic information parameters are as follows:
{{glossary}}
{{term|name}} {{defn|Most recognizable name of the site. This may or may not be the official name given by any designation registers. See [[WP:TITLE]] for more information.}}
{{quote|{{para|name|Arles Obelisk}}}}
{{term|native_name}} {{defn|The name of the site in its native language. For sites in countries that have more than one common language, choose the language most closely associated with the specific region of the country in which the site is located, and use the native_name2 and native_name3 parameters for other languages. Only three languages are supported at this time.}}
{{quote|{{para|native_name|Obélisque d'Arles}}}}
{{term|native_language}} {{defn|The language of the native name or its corresponding [[:en:ISO 639-1|ISO 639-1]], [[:en:ISO 639-2|ISO 639-2]] or [[:en:ISO 639-3|ISO 639-3]] language code. This uses the {{tl|lang}} templates to display a link to the article about the language. If a language name (e.g. "French", "Russian", etc.) is specified, {{tl|Lang2iso}} converts it into its ISO abbreviation.}}
{{quote|{{para|native_language | French}}}}
{{term|native_name2}} {{defn|The same as the native_name parameter above.}}
{{quote|{{para|native_name2|Obelisco de Arles}}}}
{{term|native_language2}} {{defn|The same as the native_language parameter above.}}
{{quote|{{para|native_language2|Spanish}} or {{para|native_language2 | es}}}}
{{term|native_name3}} {{defn|The same as the native_name parameter above.}}
{{quote|{{para|native_name3|Арль Обелиск}}}}
{{term|native_language3}} {{defn|The same as the native_language parameter above.}}
{{quote|{{para|native_language3|Russian}} or {{para|native_language3 | ru}}}}
{{term|type}} {{defn|Type of object}}
{{quote|{{para|type|burial mound}}, {{para|type|church}}}}
{{term|location}} {{defn|City, country, state, province, etc. in which site is located. If known, the postal address of the site can be included here as well. It is suggested that links are provided to the cities and countries.}}
{{quote|{{para|location|<nowiki>Place de la République<br/>13200 [[:en:Arles, France|Arles, France]]</nowiki>}}}}
{{term|area}} {{defn|Land area of the site. Mostly used with districts, parks, and other extended areas. {{tl|Convert}} tags may be used to display English alongside metric measurements.}}
{{quote|{{para|area|814 acres}}}}
{{quote|{{para|area|<nowiki>{{convert|814|acre|ha}}</nowiki>}}}}
{{term|elevation}} {{defn|Elevation above sea level. {{tl|Convert}} tags may be used to display English alongside metric measurements.}}
{{quote|{{para|elevation|2,400 ft}}}}
{{quote|{{para|elevation|<nowiki>{{convert|2400|ft}}</nowiki>}}}}
{{term|height}} {{defn|Height of designated object, if applicable. Mostly used with statues, obelisks, and some buildings. {{tl|Convert}} tags may be used to display English alongside metric measurements.}}
{{quote|{{para|elevation|151 feet 1 inch}}}}
{{quote|{{para|elevation|<nowiki>{{convert|151|ft|1|in}}</nowiki>}}}}
{{term|formed}} {{defn|If the site is a natural land formation or habitat, this parameter describes when it was formed.}}
{{quote|{{para|formed|<nowiki>[[Cretaceous period]]</nowiki>}}}}
{{term|founded}} {{defn|If the site is a city or locality which was founded by a group of people, this parameter describes when it was founded.}}
{{quote|{{para|founded|March 14, 1698}}}}
{{term|built}} {{defn|If the site is a building or manmade structure, this parameter describes when it was built.}}
{{quote|{{para|built|4th century}}}}
{{term|beginning_label}} {{defn|If none of the above labels quite apply to the article's subject (i.e. if the place was "settled" or "discovered"), this parameter can be used in conjunction with ''beginning_date'' to show a customized date.}}
{{quote|{{para|beginning_label|Settled}} and {{para|beginning_date|15th century}}}}
{{term|built_for}} {{defn|If a building or structure was built for a specific person (such as a king or queen) or organization, this parameter identifies them.}}
{{quote|{{para|built_for|King Alexander I}}}}
{{term|demolished}} {{defn|If the site is no longer standing because it has been demolished, this is the date of demolition.}}
{{quote|{{para|demolished|August 22, 2001}}}}
{{term|rebuilt}} {{defn|If the site was rebuilt after being demolished or destroyed, this is the date the site was rebuilt.}}
{{quote|{{para|rebuilt|December 14, 2007}}}}
{{term|restored}} {{defn|If the site was remodelled or restored to its original condition, this is the date of restoration.}}
{{quote|{{para|restored|January 7, 1987}}}}
{{term|restored_by}} {{defn|The person who restored or remodelled the building.}}
{{quote|{{para|restored_by|Natchez Garden Club, Inc.}}}}
{{term|architect}} {{defn|If the site is a building or manmade structure, this parameter names the architect. If Wikipedia contains an article about the architect, link to that article.}}
{{quote|{{para|architect|Jacques Peytret}}}}
{{term|architecture}} {{defn|If the site is a building or manmade structure, this parameter describes the architectural style. Links are encouraged.}}
{{quote|{{para|architecture|<nowiki>[[Classical Revival]], Other</nowiki>}}}}
{{term|visitors_num}} {{defn|Most recent figure describing the number of visitors to the site in a given year. If a specific year is not known, an estimated annual number of visitors can be included.}}
{{quote|{{para|visitors_num|81,344}}}}
{{quote|{{para|visitors_num|80,000 annually}}}}
{{term|visitors_year}} {{defn|If a specific year was used for ''visitors_num'', the year goes here. If there is a reference, include it in this parameter, making sure to properly format it.}}
{{quote|{{para|visitors_ref|<nowiki><ref>{{cite web|...}}</ref></nowiki>}}}}
{{term|governing_body}} {{defn|Body that owns/operates the historic site. If there is a Wikipedia article about the governing body, link to it. If the site is owned by a local or national government, be sure to provide adequate regional information.}}
{{quote|{{para|governing_body|<nowiki>[[Government of France]]</nowiki>}}}}
{{glossary end}}

===Image/Map===
The infobox can display both an image and a map. If an image is present, the map will be displayed at the bottom of the infobox, and if no image is specified, the map will take its place at the top of the infobox. Image/Map parameters are as follows:

====Image====
{{glossary}}
{{term|image}} {{defn|Name of main image displayed. Only the title of the image (i.e. Don't include "File:" or "Image:").}}
{{quote|{{para|image|Arles obelisque.jpg}}}}

{{term|image_size}} {{defn|Width of main image in pixels ('''Do not include "px"'''). Default 250.}}
{{quote|{{para|image_size|300}}}}

{{term|caption}} {{defn|Caption for main image. Links can be included in this text.}}
{{quote|{{para|caption|Arles Obelisk in front of the Arles Town Hall}}}}

{{term|alt}} {{defn|Alt text for image. For more information see [[WP:ALT]].}}
{{quote|{{para|alt|Obelisk in front of two buildings.}}}}
{{glossary end}}

====Site map====
{{glossary}}
{{term|image_map}} {{defn|Name of site map image displayed. Only the title of the image (i.e. Don't include "File:" or "Image:").}}
{{quote|{{para|image_map|Historic_site_plan.jpg}}}}

{{term|image_map_size}} {{defn|Width of site map image in pixels ('''Do not include "px"'''). Default 250.}}
{{quote|{{para|image_map_size|300}}}}

{{term|image_map_caption}} {{defn|Caption for site map image. Links can be included in this text.}}
{{quote|{{para|image_map_caption|Archaeological map of the historic site}}}}

{{term|image_map_alt}} {{defn|Alt text for image. For more information see [[WP:ALT]].}}
{{quote|{{para|image_map_alt|An archaeological map of the historic site with circles marking the locations of major finds}}}}
{{glossary end}}

====Map====
{{glossary}}
{{term|locmapin}} {{defn|If you want a map to be displayed, set this parameter to the region in which the site is located. See {{tl|Location map}} for valid regions. If the parameter is left blank, no map will be displayed.}}
{{quote|{{para|locmapin|France}}}}

{{term|map_relief}} {{defn|Any non-blank value (<code>yes</code>, <code>1</code>, etc.) will cause the template to display a [[:en:relief mapping (computer graphics)|relief map]] image, where available. For additional information, see [[Template:Location map#Relief parameter]].}}
{{quote|{{para|map_relief|yes}}}}

{{term|map_width}} {{defn|Width of the map in pixels ('''Do not include "px"'''). Default 235.}}
{{quote|{{para|map_width|275}}}}

{{term|map_caption}} {{defn|Caption displayed under the map. The default caption (automatically displayed) is "Location of ''name'' in ''region''", where ''name'' is controlled by the {{para|name}} parameter and ''region'' is controlled by the {{para|locmapin}} parameter. If you want to display something different, type it here. Links can be included in this text.}}
{{quote|{{para|map_caption|<nowiki>Arles Obelisk is in [[:en:Arles, France|Arles, France]]</nowiki>}}}}

{{term|map_dot_mark}} {{defn|Pin color for use on the map. Defaults to [[:File:Red pog.svg]] if left blank. See [[:Commons:Category:Map pointers, dotset 1]] for alternate images to use. }}
{{quote|{{para|map_dot_mark|Blue pog.svg}}}}

{{term|map_dot_label}} {{defn|Label for use with the pin on the map. Defaults to blank. }}
{{quote|{{para|map_dot_label|Approximate location.svg}}}}
{{glossary end}}

=====Mapframe parameters=====
{{Infobox mapframe/doc/parameters
  | mapframe-frame-width = 250
  | mapframe-type = landmark
  | onByDefault = yes, unless any of these are set: {{para|locmapin}}, {{para|image_map}}, {{para|embed}}
}}

===Coordinates===
To display the site's location on the map, coordinates are needed. Use the {{tl|Coord}} template. See the Coord template documentation for details on format, display, and other options. 

Without coordinates, the map will not display even if a value is present in <code>|&nbsp;locmapin =</code>.

=== Grid references ===
For sites in Great Britain an [[:en:British national grid reference system|Ordnance Survey grid reference]] may be given. Spaces are allowed - see [[template:OS coord/doc|details of format]].
::'''Example –''' <code>|&nbsp;gbgridref = TQ 306 815</code>

